36. Democr. would have had good reason to laugh. had he seen the pompa circeum, with praetor or consul presiding in state. This procession, which preceded the races in the Circus, marched from the Capitol through the Forum and the Velabrum and round the Circus itself. At the head, surrounded by musicians and cliente, came the president of tbe ganea, whether consul or praetor, driving in a chariot and wearing the dress of a triumphing general. Images os the gods and statues ‘oi the imperial family were borne along in the procession.
